1. DEFINITIONS

"Software" refers to the Fibonacci Delta Encoding Engine (FDEE) source code and the proprietary "Index ± Offset" algorithmic implementation. "Public Project" refers to any software, research, or service that is accessible, visible, or marketed to the general public or a specific industry.

2. GRANT OF LICENSE

A. Academic and Personal Use:
The Software may be used for non-commercial research free of charge, provided that the Attribution requirements are met.

B. Mandatory Usage Notification (The "Curiosity" Clause):
Regardless of whether the use is commercial or academic, if the Software is integrated into a Public Project, the User MUST notify the Author via email (tudor@ipsilo.eu) within 30 days of deployment or publication. This notification should include:

The name of the project.

A brief description of how FDEE is being utilized.

A link to the project or associated documentation.

C. Commercial Use:
Commercial use is STRICTLY PROHIBITED without a separate, written Commercial License Agreement.

3. ETHICAL CLAUSE

The Author reserves the right to revoke use permissions for any entity or project deemed to be acting against the ethical advancement of humanity. The Software must be used in a way that is safe, healthy, and beneficial to society. Use of the Software for harmful, illegal, or destructive purposes is a violation of this license.

4. RESTRICTIONS & INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

The "Index ± Offset" logic remains the sole intellectual property of the Author. Unauthorized commercial use or failure to notify the author of public deployment constitutes a breach of this agreement.

5. TERMINATION

